==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Easting
<hw>East"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut. & Surv.)</fld> <def>The
distance measured toward the east between two meridians drawn through
the extremities of a course; distance of departure eastward made by a
vessel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>East-insular</ent>⟦br⟧
